1. sudo apt-get install npm
2. sudo npm install -g express
3. sudo npm install -g express-generator
4. express nodetest1 - start a new project (express does the scaffolding)
5. package.json - add mongodb and monk "*" - latest version
6. sudo npm install - for installing dependencies (express, mongodb, monk - creates routes / views folders etc.)
7. mkdir data - for mongodb
8. npm start
9. localhost:3000 you will see the page
10. mongod and mongo setup
   mongod --dbpath nodetest1/data --port 9160
   mongo --port 9160
   use nodetest1
   